### Get root endpoint
GET {{baseUrl}}/

### Get info endpoint
GET {{baseUrl}}/info

### Get authenticated route (unauthorized)
GET {{baseUrl}}/authenticated-route

### Register a new user
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "password": "password123",
  "first_name": "Test",
  "last_name": "User"
}

### Login user
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/jwt/login
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

username=test@example.com&password=password123

### Get authenticated route (authorized)
# First get the token from login, then use it in the header
GET {{baseUrl}}/authenticated-route
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Get user
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/me
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Update user
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/users/me
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "first_name": "Updated",
  "last_name": "User"
}

### Logout
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/jwt/logout
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

